@{
ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<body>
    <div class="grid-container">
        <header>
            <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

            Weapon Accounting Project
            Effective Date: 04.02.25
        </header>

        <aside id="left-menu" class="home-left-menu">
            <h3>FAQ</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#">How to use this site?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Make local database!</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Upload weapons from exel</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">PDF reports</a></li>
            </ul>
        </aside>

        <main>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Introduction</h2>

                    Welcome to Weapon Accounting Project. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our system.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Information We Collect</h2>

                    We may collect the following types of information:

                    Personal Information: Name, email address, phone number, and user credentials.

                    Weapon Details: Serial numbers, model, manufacturer, and ownership records.

                    Usage Data: Logins, transactions, and audit logs.

                    Device Information: IP address, browser type, and access times.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">How We Use Your Information</h2>

                    We use collected data to:

                    Manage and track weapon inventory.

                    Authenticate users and control access.

                    Ensure compliance with regulations.

                    Improve system security and performance.

                    Provide customer support.
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Data Protection and Security</h2>

                    We take reasonable measures to protect your information, including encryption, access controls, and secure storage.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>

                    We do not sell or rent your personal data. However, we may share information with:

                    Law Enforcement Agencies when required by law.

                    Authorized Government Bodies for regulatory compliance.

                    Service Providers that help us operate and maintain the system.
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Your Rights and Choices</h2>

                    You have the right to:

                    Access and update your personal information.

                    Request deletion of certain data, subject to legal obligations.

                    Opt-out of non-essential data collection where applicable.
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Data Retention</h2>

                    We retain data as long as necessary for legal compliance, security, and operational purposes. Upon request, we may delete or anonymize data as required by law.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

                    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the updated policy on our website.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <h2 class="privacy-header">Contact Information</h2>

                    If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

                    Email: [Contact Email]

                    Phone: [Contact Number]

                    By using the Weapon Accounting Project, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </main>
    </div>
</body>
